In [ ]:
from matplotlib import legend
import pandas as pd

maleDataFrame = df.loc[(df['sex']==1) & (df['age'] == 20)]
femaleDataFrame = df.loc[(df['sex']==2) & (df['age'] == 20)]

tab10 = plt.get_cmap('tab10')

ax = plt.subplot()

femaleDataFrame.plot(x='year', y='people', kind='line', color=tab10(6),ax = ax, label='Female')
maleDataFrame.plot(x='year', y='people', kind='line', color=tab10(0), ax = ax, label='Male')

ax.legend()

ax.figure.set_figheight(7)
ax.figure.set_figwidth(15)

ax.set_xlabel('Year [Decade]')
ax.set_ylabel('People [Per Million]')
ax.set_title('Male Vs Female Population')
Out[ ]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Male Vs Female Population')

I've used tab10 since we don't need that much of a range in the colormap, I've mapped the color blue to indicate male and pink to indicate female as it has been generalised since ages.
